    {
      "id": "task-zoom-bands-semantic-zoom",
      "type": "markdown",
      "label": "Zoom Bands",
      "position": {
        "x": 420,
        "y": -260
      },
      "width": 420,
      "height": 260,
      "visible": true,
      "showLabel": true,
      "data": {
        "markdown": "# Zoom Bands\n\nPhysical zoom should still matter, but semantic zoom should be led by navigation focus.\n\nCandidate semantic levels:\n\n- `detail` for the focused fragment\n- `summary` for directly linked fragments\n- `icon` for deeper linked graphs\n\nPhysical zoom can bias how much detail is practical, but navigation determines which fragment deserves attention.",
        "_classBinding": {
          "key": "markdown",
          "sourceRef": "github://twilite-zone/public/library/classes/nodes/markdown.node-class.node",
          "ref": "github://twilite-zone/public/library/classes/nodes/markdown.node-class.node",
          "identity": {
