    {
      "id": "task-fallbacks-semantic-zoom",
      "type": "markdown",
      "label": "Fallback Rules",
      "position": {
        "x": 420,
        "y": 80
      },
      "width": 420,
      "height": 320,
      "visible": true,
      "showLabel": true,
      "data": {
        "markdown": "# Fallback Rules\n\nFallback should be deterministic, relative to the focused fragment, and automatic by default.\n\nRules:\n\n- focused fragment uses the resolved base representation\n- linked fragments render one level lower if available\n- deeper fragments render two levels lower if available\n- if a requested level is missing, fall back to the nearest lower valid representation for that role\n- if no authored or automatic representation exists, use the minimal generic graph-object badge/card\n\nPeripheral fragments must never become more visually prominent than the focus.",
        "_classBinding": {
          "key": "markdown",
          "sourceRef": "github://twilite-zone/public/library/classes/nodes/markdown.node-class.node",
          "ref": "github://twilite-zone/public/library/classes/nodes/markdown.node-class.node",
          "identity": {
