    {
      "id": "task-local-fragments-semantic-zoom",
      "type": "markdown",
      "label": "Local Fragment Opportunity",
      "position": {
        "x": 920,
        "y": 460
      },
      "width": 420,
      "height": 280,
      "visible": true,
      "showLabel": true,
      "data": {
        "markdown": "# Local Fragment Opportunity\n\nA likely insertion point is **inside a single graph**, not only between graphs.\n\nUse local fragments as units of reveal so dense graphs can become exploratory instead of overloaded.\n\nCurrent default split:\n\n- local fragments enter at `summary` / medium detail\n- external graphs enter at `icon`\n\nThat keeps nearby structure legible without letting referenced graphs compete with the current canvas.",
        "_classBinding": {
          "key": "markdown",
          "sourceRef": "github://twilite-zone/public/library/classes/nodes/markdown.node-class.node",
