    {
      "id": "task-local-vs-external-semantic-zoom",
      "type": "markdown",
      "label": "Local vs External Default",
      "position": {
        "x": 920,
        "y": 780
      },
      "width": 420,
      "height": 260,
      "visible": true,
      "showLabel": true,
      "data": {
        "markdown": "# Local vs External Default\n\nDefault semantic policy:\n\n- **local fragment** = `summary`\n- **external graph** = `icon`\n\nReasoning:\n\n- local fragments are part of the active thought surface and should arrive legibly\n- external graphs are references first and should enter quietly unless promoted by context\n\nTreat this as the default, not an unbreakable law.",
        "_classBinding": {
