    {
      "id": "task-port-visibility-semantic-zoom",
      "type": "markdown",
      "label": "Port Visibility By Semantic Level",
      "position": {
        "x": 1400,
        "y": 780
      },
      "width": 440,
      "height": 300,
      "visible": true,
      "showLabel": true,
      "data": {
        "markdown": "# Port Visibility By Semantic Level\n\nPort declarations stay stable. What changes with semantic zoom is **manifestation**.\n\n- `detail`: ports may be fully visible and interactable\n- `summary`: ports may be reduced to hints or selectively shown\n- `icon`: ports should not appear as full handles; at most use latent connection hints\n\nThis makes ports a semantic-zoom concern as well as a handle-layer concern.",
        "_classBinding": {
