    {
      "id": "task-focused-node-semantic-zoom",
      "type": "markdown",
      "label": "Focused Node",
      "position": {
        "x": 920,
        "y": -260
      },
      "width": 420,
      "height": 260,
      "visible": true,
      "showLabel": true,
      "data": {
        "markdown": "# Focused Node\n\nTwilite needs a `focused node` distinct from the selected node.\n\nSelection is an editing state. Focus is a navigation state.\n\nThe focused node determines which graph fragment is primary, but it does not guarantee absolute detail. The focused fragment can itself be rendered at different semantic levels depending on navigation and zoom pressure. Other fragments should step down relative to that level.",
        "_classBinding": {
          "key": "markdown",
          "sourceRef": "github://twilite-zone/public/library/classes/nodes/markdown.node-class.node",
          "ref": "github://twilite-zone/public/library/classes/nodes/markdown.node-class.node",
          "identity": {
            "graphId": "markdown_class",
            "name": "markdown Node Class",
            "version": "0.1.0",
            "description": "Canonical markdown content node.",
            "createdAt": "2026-02-24T20:05:15Z",
            "updatedAt": "2026-03-24T01:20:00.000Z"
          },
          "intent": "graph",
          "meaning": "Canonical markdown content node.",
          "description": "Canonical markdown content node.",
          "defaults": {},
          "nodeDef": {
            "key": "markdown",
            "ref": "github://twilite-zone/public/library/classes/nodes/markdown.node-class.node",
            "source": "local",
            "version": ">=0.1.0"
          },
