    },
    {
      "id": "task-fragment-cascade-semantic-zoom",
      "type": "markdown",
      "label": "Fragment Cascade",
      "position": {
        "x": 920,
        "y": 460
      },
      "width": 420,
      "height": 360,
      "visible": true,
      "showLabel": true,
      "data": {
        "markdown": "# Fragment Cascade\n\nSemantic zoom should cascade through linked fragments *relative to the current focus level*.\n\n- focused fragment: `focus level`\n- directly linked fragments: `focus level - 1`\n- deeper linked graphs: `focus level - 2`\n\nThis means if the user zooms the focused fragment down to icon-level representation, peripheral fragments step down with it rather than staying louder than the focus.",
        "_classBinding": {
          "key": "markdown",
