    {
      "id": "task-relative-levels-semantic-zoom",
      "type": "markdown",
      "label": "Relative Semantic Levels",
      "position": {
        "x": 1360,
        "y": 80
      },
      "width": 420,
      "height": 320,
      "visible": true,
      "showLabel": true,
      "data": {
        "markdown": "# Relative Semantic Levels\n\nSemantic zoom levels should be relative, not absolute.\n\nInstead of saying:\n- focused = detail\n- linked = summary\n- deep = icon\n\nThe system should say:\n- focused fragment = current semantic level\n- linked fragment = current level - 1\n- deeper fragment = current level - 2\n\nThis prevents the periphery from becoming visually louder than the user's current focus.",
        "_classBinding": {
          "key": "markdown",
          "sourceRef": "github://twilite-zone/public/library/classes/nodes/markdown.node-class.node",
          "ref": "github://twilite-zone/public/library/classes/nodes/markdown.node-class.node",
