    {
      "id": "task-graph-canvas-vs-object-semantic-zoom",
      "type": "markdown",
      "label": "Graph As Canvas vs Object",
      "position": {
        "x": 2840,
        "y": -260
      },
      "width": 460,
      "height": 340,
      "visible": true,
      "showLabel": true,
      "data": {
        "markdown": "# Graph As Canvas vs Object\n\nA `.node` graph is the same artifact in both cases, but it can appear in two different rendering roles:\n\n- **graph-as-canvas**: the active workspace you are inside\n- **graph-as-object**: a representation of that graph inside another graph\n\nSemantic zoom must account for this distinction. The artifact is the same; the rendering role is different.",
        "_classBinding": {
          "key": "markdown",
          "sourceRef": "github://twilite-zone/public/library/classes/nodes/markdown.node-class.node",
          "ref": "github://twilite-zone/public/library/classes/nodes/markdown.node-class.node",
          "identity": {
            "graphId": "markdown_class",
