    {
      "id": "task-class-graph-vs-node-instance-semantic-zoom",
      "type": "markdown",
      "label": "Class Graph vs Node Instance",
      "position": {
        "x": 3360,
        "y": -260
      },
      "width": 480,
      "height": 380,
      "visible": true,
      "showLabel": true,
      "data": {
        "markdown": "# Class Graph vs Node Instance\n\nA node class and a node instance are not the same thing.\n\n- **class graph**: a `.node` graph that defines a reusable type\n- **node instance**: a host-graph node that uses that type\n\nThe class graph may contain a manifest, dictionary, view definitions, schema, and behavior. The node instance does not become a graph context just because it is backed by a class graph. It remains a node in the host graph unless the class graph itself is referenced or rendered as a graph-object.",
        "_classBinding": {
          "key": "markdown",
          "sourceRef": "github://twilite-zone/public/library/classes/nodes/markdown.node-class.node",
          "ref": "github://twilite-zone/public/library/classes/nodes/markdown.node-class.node",
          "identity": {
            "graphId": "markdown_class",
            "name": "markdown Node Class",
            "version": "0.1.0",
            "description": "Canonical markdown content node.",
            "createdAt": "2026-02-24T20:05:15Z",
            "updatedAt": "2026-03-24T01:20:00.000Z"
          },
          "intent": "graph",
          "meaning": "Canonical markdown content node.",
          "description": "Canonical markdown content node.",
          "defaults": {},
          "nodeDef": {
