    {
      "id": "task-node-vs-graph-representation-semantic-zoom",
      "type": "markdown",
      "label": "Node vs Graph Representation",
      "position": {
        "x": 3360,
        "y": 180
      },
      "width": 480,
      "height": 360,
      "visible": true,
      "showLabel": true,
      "data": {
        "markdown": "# Node vs Graph Representation\n\nRepresentation family depends on what is being rendered:\n\n- node instance -> `node.*` representations\n- graph represented inside another graph -> `graph.*` representations\n- active graph workspace -> canvas rendering\n\nA class graph can define both families, but they apply in different roles. The instance uses the node family. The referenced graph uses the graph family.",
        "_classBinding": {
          "key": "markdown",
          "sourceRef": "github://twilite-zone/public/library/classes/nodes/markdown.node-class.node",
