    {
      "id": "task-explicit-views-as-overrides-semantic-zoom",
      "type": "markdown",
      "label": "Explicit Views As Overrides",
      "position": {
        "x": 3880,
        "y": 180
      },
      "width": 480,
      "height": 340,
      "visible": true,
      "showLabel": true,
      "data": {
        "markdown": "# Explicit Views As Overrides\n\nExplicit semantic views are where graphs and node classes become expressive.\n\nPolicy:\n\n- baseline semantic zoom comes from runtime fallback/derivation\n- authored `detail`, `summary`, and `icon` views override the baseline\n- automatic fallback stays simple and structural\n- authored views may be richer, more domain-specific, and more visually intentional\n- users should never see blank or broken representations just because a semantic view was never authored",
        "_classBinding": {
          "key": "markdown",
          "sourceRef": "github://twilite-zone/public/library/classes/nodes/markdown.node-class.node",
          "ref": "github://twilite-zone/public/library/classes/nodes/markdown.node-class.node",
