    {
      "id": "task-browse-default-without-toolbar-semantic-zoom",
      "type": "markdown",
      "label": "Browse Default Without Toolbar",
      "position": {
        "x": 5960,
        "y": 560
      },
      "width": 520,
      "height": 300,
      "visible": true,
      "showLabel": true,
      "data": {
        "markdown": "# Browse Default Without Toolbar\n\nIf the toolbar/editor chrome is absent, Twilite should default to browse mode.\n\nThat fits the viewer/embedded/runtime posture:\n\n- read\n- navigate\n- traverse linked graphs\n- inspect graph objects\n\nEditing should not be the implicit default in minimal or embedded contexts.",
