    {
      "id": "task-keyboard-command-layer-semantic-zoom",
      "type": "markdown",
      "label": "Keyboard As Command Layer",
      "position": {
        "x": 6480,
        "y": 140
      },
      "width": 520,
      "height": 340,
      "visible": true,
      "showLabel": true,
      "data": {
        "markdown": "# Keyboard As Command Layer\n\nKeyboard remains useful, but not as the main graph browsing mechanism.\n\nGood keyboard roles:\n\n- mode switching\n- delete / duplicate / copy / paste\n- search / command palette\n- confirm / cancel\n- open / back / forward commands\n\nKeyboard should support graph work without pretending to be the primary spatial navigation tool.",
        "_classBinding": {
          "key": "markdown",
          "sourceRef": "github://twilite-zone/public/library/classes/nodes/markdown.node-class.node",
