    {
      "id": "task-focused-fragment-containment-semantic-zoom",
      "type": "markdown",
      "label": "Focused Fragment Containment",
      "position": {
        "x": 7000,
        "y": 180
      },
      "width": 540,
      "height": 340,
      "visible": true,
      "showLabel": true,
      "data": {
        "markdown": "# Focused Fragment Containment\n\nThe focused fragment is the fragment that contains the focused node.\n\nThat means:\n\n- node focus is the local anchor\n- fragment focus is derived from node containment\n\nThis keeps the focus model coherent and prevents node focus and fragment focus from drifting apart.",
        "_classBinding": {
          "key": "markdown",
          "sourceRef": "github://twilite-zone/public/library/classes/nodes/markdown.node-class.node",
          "ref": "github://twilite-zone/public/library/classes/nodes/markdown.node-class.node",
