    {
      "id": "task-nearest-lower-fallback-semantic-zoom",
      "type": "markdown",
      "label": "Nearest Lower Fallback",
      "position": {
        "x": 7520,
        "y": -260
      },
      "width": 560,
      "height": 380,
      "visible": true,
      "showLabel": true,
      "data": {
        "markdown": "# Nearest Lower Fallback\n\nIf the requested semantic representation does not exist, the runtime should fall back to the nearest lower valid representation for that role.\n\nRules:\n\n- never promote peripheral content above the focused fragment's relative prominence\n- prefer automatic representations before generic fallback\n- if `focus-1` is missing, use automatic summary or icon as appropriate\n- if `focus-2` is missing, use automatic icon\n- if nothing richer exists, use the minimal generic graph-object badge/card\n\nThis keeps semantic reduction stable even when authored views are sparse.",
        "_classBinding": {
          "key": "markdown",
          "sourceRef": "github://twilite-zone/public/library/classes/nodes/markdown.node-class.node",
          "ref": "github://twilite-zone/public/library/classes/nodes/markdown.node-class.node",
          "identity": {
